      <description>Hangar 9 RC Kit Plane Nitro Because it is not safe to reuse a lid used to seal canned another canning jar, which can used with all caps? It may not seem a major problem for the pan occasionally at home that puts a couple of batches of tomato marmalade and jam every year. If [...]&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://rcrtf.com/hangar-9-rc-kit-plane-nitro/"&gt;Hangar 9 RC Kit Plane Nitro&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://rcrtf.com"&gt;RC RTF&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/rc-rtf/RC_RTF-Hangar_9_RC_Kit_Plane_Nitro.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><strong>Hangar 9 RC Kit Plane Nitro</strong></p>
<p> Because it is not safe to reuse a lid used to seal canned another canning jar, which can used with all caps? It may not seem a major problem for the pan occasionally at home that puts a couple of batches of tomato marmalade and jam every year. </p>
<p> If you get into the habit still a lot of things that end up with a bunch of tapes used. Instead of throwing garbage and landfill problems, here are ten creative ideas for reuse lids used to pack. </p>
<p> 1. Mobile <br /> Paint the tops of bright colors. Make a hole through the lid of a 1 / 4 inch the edge. League thread at the top and then the hanger. </p>
<p> 2. game to couples <br /> Create a matching game. Print each of two letters, numbers, animal figures, shapes, colors, characters, etc. Cut and paste these items on one side of the lid. </p>
<p> 3. Wind bell <br /> Drill a small hole near the shore that is wide enough for the chain to pass through. File the sharp edges that created the drill while boring through the lid. String together in different levels, but close enough so that they touch each other. Alternatively, you can spray paint the different colors of caps before joining. </p>
<p> 4. children toy <br /> Bores a small hole near the edge that is wide enough to pass through the chain. File the sharp edges that created the drill while boring through the lid. string using tape or rope to tie the tops together. Do not use caps or oxidized paint. The painting can detach. </p>
<p> 5. Scarecrow <br /> Polish lids with # 0000 steel wool to give them a nice shine bright. That hanged with a rope around the garden to prevent the birds. </p>
<p> 6. Fridge magnets <br /> Print photos of the family. Cut to fit the lid. Paste the picture to the lid and a small flat magnet on the back of the lid. They make great Christmas and birthday gifts for grandparents day. </p>
<p> 7. Mix in a jar <br /> Prepare the mixture dry for a family favorite recipe (cookies, cakes, baked beans, etc..) discount retailers sell cheap canning jars. Fill jars with dry mixing board canning lid and ring used. </p>
<p> 8. Dry Goods Storage <br /> Used lids work well for sealing glass jars filled with dry pasta, sugar, flowers, noodles, etc. You do not need a sealed vacuum, a sufficient seal to keep out dust and woodworm. </p>
<p> 9. Christmas Yard Art <br /> Drill or punch two small holes in the ends. Spray paint lids or suede leather. String together in series. Another idea is creating combo with garland of 3-5-7 from the main chain. </p>
<p> 10. Christmas ornaments <br /> Performs a series of Christmas ornaments from the eyelids to the drilling patterns on the lid. Be creative by drilling patterns such as puppets snow, snowflakes, Santa Claus, Christmas tree, cross, etc. Enjoy and tail to fit the circumference of the outer lid. </p>
<p> I hope these ideas will provide some creative uses of the tapes used for packaging. Canning lids do not have enough to do these crafts? </p>
<p>Follow these simple canning instructions an you will be on your way to canning and storing up vegetables, jams, jellies and fruit.</p>
<p>For more canning and preserving ideas sign up for my free canning and preserving mini course that is full of tips, advice and canning recipes.</p>
<p>Hangar 9 RC Kit Plane Nitro<br />
